# Server changes → restart the API

Express/Parse run in a normal Node process — **there is no hot reload for `/server`**.

**After you edit anything under `/server`**, restart the API in the same session so the running process loads the new code (unless the user explicitly says not to).

- From repo root: `NODE_ENV=development npm start` (this project’s dev server is typically **port 8080**).
- If something is already bound to that port, stop it first, then start again (e.g. `lsof -ti:8080 2>/dev/null | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null`, then `npm start`). Match whatever the user already uses in their terminals if it differs.

The React app on port 3000 hot-reloads on its own; **only the backend needs a manual restart**.
